00:18:53.320 --> 00:18:56.490
as quickly is due to unconscious
biases that we may hold.

00:18:56.490 --> 00:18:58.860
And Google has, like I
think many companies,

00:18:58.860 --> 00:19:01.680
we have an unconscious
bias training

00:19:01.680 --> 00:19:04.060
that all employees have to take.

00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:06.030
But I know that you've
actually spoken out,

00:19:06.030 --> 00:19:07.500
saying that you
don't necessarily

00:19:07.500 --> 00:19:11.640
believe in having a mandatory
unconscious bias training.

00:19:11.640 --> 00:19:15.610
Can you speak to why that is
and what might work better?

00:19:15.610 --> 00:19:18.540
CAROL FULP: Well,
I don't personally

00:19:18.540 --> 00:19:22.980
want to go to a class
called unconscious bias.

00:19:22.980 --> 00:19:26.430
I think that the
term makes you feel--

00:19:26.430 --> 00:19:29.220
it puts you-- it
makes you tense.

00:19:29.220 --> 00:19:36.060
And so I do want to
go to a forum, a class

00:19:36.060 --> 00:19:38.440
on leading for the future.

00:19:38.440 --> 00:19:42.510
And that's what we call our
forums at the partnership,

00:19:42.510 --> 00:19:45.490
leading for the future.

00:19:45.490 --> 00:19:50.400
And so we talk about,
what does that look like?

00:19:50.400 --> 00:19:52.990
What does the
population look like?

00:19:52.990 --> 00:19:55.920
What are the technologies
going to look like?

00:19:55.920 --> 00:19:59.700
There is so much change.

00:19:59.700 --> 00:20:04.920
And because there
is so much change,

00:20:04.920 --> 00:20:11.230
what would get in the way
of us accepting this change?

00:20:11.230 --> 00:20:15.330
And so we begin to peel
back the onion that way.

00:20:15.330 --> 00:20:18.480
And that's how we get
at unconscious bias.

00:20:18.480 --> 00:20:23.880
But I find uncomfortable going
to a session called unconscious

00:20:23.880 --> 00:20:24.780
bias.

00:20:24.780 --> 00:20:29.700
I'd much rather go to a session
called leading for the future,

00:20:29.700 --> 00:20:32.880
because all of us want
to be good leaders.

00:20:32.880 --> 00:20:34.920
And then we find
out, OK, well, what

00:20:34.920 --> 00:20:39.340
might get in the way of
us being a good leader?

00:20:39.340 --> 00:20:43.230
And something that gets in the
way of us being a good leader

00:20:43.230 --> 00:20:48.040
is this unconscious
bias, which we all have.

00:20:48.040 --> 00:20:51.540
And one of the things
that I always do is,

00:20:51.540 --> 00:20:56.040
in this leading for
the future forum,

00:20:56.040 --> 00:20:59.160
is I tell people of my bias.

00:20:59.160 --> 00:21:02.010
When I walked into
the partnership,

00:21:02.010 --> 00:21:04.500
the partnership had all women.

00:21:04.500 --> 00:21:08.020
And I love being a woman.

00:21:08.020 --> 00:21:15.640
And so the personal side of me
was most comfortable with that.

00:21:15.640 --> 00:21:22.590
But I also knew that I
was missing something

00:21:22.590 --> 00:21:26.380
from an organizational
standpoint.

00:21:26.380 --> 00:21:30.750
And so my first
few hires were men.

00:21:30.750 --> 00:21:35.190
And my culture shifted
in the organization.

00:21:35.190 --> 00:21:37.170
It expanded.

00:21:37.170 --> 00:21:41.660
We had perspectives
that were not there.

00:21:41.660 --> 00:21:44.900
And so my organization
was better

00:21:44.900 --> 00:21:49.250
because we opened
up the organization

00:21:49.250 --> 00:21:52.070
so that it was more diverse.

00:21:52.070 --> 00:21:55.970
And while we're an
organization that

00:21:55.970 --> 00:22:01.130
focuses on ethnic diversity,
we have individuals

00:22:01.130 --> 00:22:05.780
who are white who work
in our organization,

00:22:05.780 --> 00:22:11.570
because I don't want to
have one of any kind.

00:22:11.570 --> 00:22:15.500
I want our organization to
be reflective of the world,

00:22:15.500 --> 00:22:18.040
to be reflective
of organizations,

00:22:18.040 --> 00:22:22.370
and we are going
to build together.

00:22:22.370 --> 00:22:27.530
So unconscious bias--
first, let's think about

00:22:27.530 --> 00:22:32.870
why and who we are and
what our own biases are.

00:22:32.870 --> 00:22:36.110
And let's check them
at the door before we

00:22:36.110 --> 00:22:38.332
come into the organization.

00:22:38.332 --> 00:22:39.290
SPEAKER 1: I love that.

00:22:39.290 --> 00:22:42.253
You should teach our
