00:22:44.420 --> 00:22:46.760
That was really thoughtful.

00:22:46.760 --> 00:22:48.803
Thank you for sharing that.

00:22:48.803 --> 00:22:50.720
I know that you were
speaking about your goals

00:22:50.720 --> 00:22:53.510
for the partnership
and your employees

00:22:53.510 --> 00:22:56.810
and what you would like
to see reflected there.

00:22:56.810 --> 00:22:58.410
We, as a company--

00:22:58.410 --> 00:23:00.560
and I'm sure many
companies-- are also

00:23:00.560 --> 00:23:03.740
trying to diversify the pipeline
and make sure that we've

00:23:03.740 --> 00:23:04.810
got talent coming in.

00:23:04.810 --> 00:23:08.030
But a lot of times, folks say,
well, there's just not there.

00:23:08.030 --> 00:23:09.800
We're looking for this
role and we're not

00:23:09.800 --> 00:23:13.070
seeing a lot of minority
groups represented

00:23:13.070 --> 00:23:15.590
for this specific role or job.

00:23:15.590 --> 00:23:17.180
What do you say to that?

00:23:17.180 --> 00:23:20.060
And how would you
challenge folks to resolve

00:23:20.060 --> 00:23:21.672
that issue for their company?

00:23:21.672 --> 00:23:23.630
CAROL FULP: Well, first
of all, let me tell you

00:23:23.630 --> 00:23:28.820
that I don't use the word
minority, because in the world,

00:23:28.820 --> 00:23:32.030
people of color are
not the minority.

00:23:32.030 --> 00:23:39.330
In Boston, people of color
are 54% of the population.

00:23:39.330 --> 00:23:41.360
So we're not the minority.

00:23:41.360 --> 00:23:45.920
So I call us people of
color rather than minority.

00:23:45.920 --> 00:23:50.150
And the word minority has a
certain connotation as well.

00:23:50.150 --> 00:23:54.870
So I use the word
people of color.

00:23:54.870 --> 00:24:00.450
So I encourage people
to do that as well.

00:24:00.450 --> 00:24:04.880
And I encourage people to
move beyond the traditional

00:24:04.880 --> 00:24:08.780
recruiting sources.

00:24:08.780 --> 00:24:11.480
We have 4,000
individuals who have

00:24:11.480 --> 00:24:16.700
been through the partnership
training programs.

00:24:16.700 --> 00:24:21.860
Next month, Carmen will
be training over 250,

00:24:21.860 --> 00:24:24.800
I think you have starting.

00:24:24.800 --> 00:24:32.600
There are people who are
in our greater Boston area.

00:24:32.600 --> 00:24:37.280
You have to look beyond
the traditional sources.

00:24:37.280 --> 00:24:40.610
You went to Howard University.

00:24:40.610 --> 00:24:47.180
There is a Howard University
alumni chapter here in Boston.

00:24:47.180 --> 00:24:49.610
That's a great place to start.

00:24:49.610 --> 00:24:54.890
Here at the partnership,
we've created a job board

00:24:54.890 --> 00:24:59.060
for companies who want
to be able to advertise

00:24:59.060 --> 00:25:06.290
their jobs through us, because
individuals know that people

00:25:06.290 --> 00:25:11.990
who are advertising on the
partnership's job board website

00:25:11.990 --> 00:25:15.780
really value diversity.

00:25:15.780 --> 00:25:21.020
So there are ways that
you can approach and find

00:25:21.020 --> 00:25:24.120
and resource people of color.

00:25:24.120 --> 00:25:27.530
One of the strategies
that I mention in the book

00:25:27.530 --> 00:25:29.870
is the Rooney rule.

00:25:29.870 --> 00:25:34.900
And that is to say that
when you have a job

00:25:34.900 --> 00:25:42.830
open to ensure that you
interview diverse talent.

00:25:42.830 --> 00:25:47.690
You don't fill that job unless
you have a diverse pool.

00:25:47.690 --> 00:25:52.070
Now, we're not telling you
to hire a diverse talent.

00:25:52.070 --> 00:25:57.350
But we're telling you to make
sure that the pool is diverse.

00:25:57.350 --> 00:26:02.120
And this rule
comes from the NFL,

00:26:02.120 --> 00:26:05.750
when they tried to
increase diversity

00:26:05.750 --> 00:26:09.540
amongst their coaches.

00:26:09.540 --> 00:26:15.830
And it just so happened
that they were at its peak

00:26:15.830 --> 00:26:21.650
when, one Super Bowl, they had
two African-Americans playing

00:26:21.650 --> 00:26:25.550
against each other, two coaches.

00:26:25.550 --> 00:26:30.620
But for a long time,
there was no coaches

00:26:30.620 --> 00:26:32.750
who were African-American.

00:26:32.750 --> 00:26:34.640
Now, we still have
a long way to go.

00:26:34.640 --> 00:26:38.940
And we still have a long
way to go with the NFL.

00:26:38.940 --> 00:26:44.070
But the Rooney rule is
really an opportunity for us

00:26:44.070 --> 00:26:47.770
to ensure our pools are diverse.

00:26:47.770 --> 00:26:52.770
Managers can select whomever,
but at least we're seeing,

00:26:52.770 --> 00:26:58.040
we're being intentional about
seeing candidates of color.

00:26:58.040 --> 00:27:00.370
SPEAKER 1: That
