00:27:16.138 --> 00:27:17.805
CAROL FULP: Oh, that's
a great question.

00:27:20.740 --> 00:27:26.130
Well, I think the some
of the biggest challenges

00:27:26.130 --> 00:27:36.840
were finding companies
that had really excelled

00:27:36.840 --> 00:27:40.590
and were exceptional.

00:27:40.590 --> 00:27:46.160
And I was able to find
Hallmark Health, who

00:27:46.160 --> 00:27:53.610
had used the Rooney rule and
seen their profits go up.

00:27:53.610 --> 00:27:55.850
So it's one thing to
use the Rooney rule,

00:27:55.850 --> 00:27:59.550
but I wanted to be able to
relate that to profitability.

00:27:59.550 --> 00:28:01.970
And so when
interviewing their CEO,

00:28:01.970 --> 00:28:06.060
they attributed that
to their profitability.

00:28:06.060 --> 00:28:08.550
So I was glad to see that.

00:28:08.550 --> 00:28:14.600
And then the other
challenge was to be

00:28:14.600 --> 00:28:25.370
able to find CEOs who
would be able to indicate

00:28:25.370 --> 00:28:27.860
what they did wrong.

00:28:27.860 --> 00:28:32.450
And none of us want to
indicate what we did wrong.

00:28:32.450 --> 00:28:34.690
And so those were the
biggest challenges.

00:28:34.690 --> 00:28:36.730
But that's a great question.

00:28:36.730 --> 00:28:37.597
So thank you.

00:28:37.597 --> 00:28:38.430
AUDIENCE: Hi, there.

00:28:38.430 --> 00:28:39.650
Thanks for coming today.

00:28:39.650 --> 00:28:41.390
CAROL FULP: Hi.

00:28:41.390 --> 00:28:44.000
AUDIENCE: I was curious, as
you were doing your research,

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:48.390
was there a certain industry
