00:28:55.280 --> 00:28:58.400
from other industries that might
be doing it better than ours?

00:28:58.400 --> 00:29:01.370
And along those
lines, if they are

00:29:01.370 --> 00:29:03.437
successful in their
recruiting methods,

00:29:03.437 --> 00:29:06.020
is there something they partner
with retention methods as well

00:29:06.020 --> 00:29:07.910
that helps them be successful?

00:29:07.910 --> 00:29:13.400
CAROL FULP: Yeah, I found
that the finance industry

00:29:13.400 --> 00:29:16.340
is particularly good
at it, because they've

00:29:16.340 --> 00:29:21.080
been doing it a longer
period of time, number one.

00:29:21.080 --> 00:29:26.090
And recruiting is certainly
linked to retention.

00:29:26.090 --> 00:29:30.350
And there's one finance
company that has

00:29:30.350 --> 00:29:35.630
27 ERGs in their organizations.

00:29:35.630 --> 00:29:37.550
Do you know what ERGs are?

00:29:37.550 --> 00:29:39.470
Employee resource groups.

00:29:39.470 --> 00:29:41.300
27.

00:29:41.300 --> 00:29:46.190
So they have a resource
group for every difference.

00:29:46.190 --> 00:29:53.580
So people feel valued
there and that they can--

00:29:53.580 --> 00:29:55.820
their difference is valued.

00:29:55.820 --> 00:30:01.970
It's supported by their company,
and that they think twice

00:30:01.970 --> 00:30:07.310
about leaving, because
ERGs are really

00:30:07.310 --> 00:30:10.350
a core part of the business.

00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:15.320
The other thing that I found
is that ERGs are merging,

00:30:15.320 --> 00:30:20.060
are moving towards
business resource groups.

00:30:20.060 --> 00:30:22.620
So the Mattel story--

00:30:22.620 --> 00:30:26.510
so it's just not an
ERG now, that companies

00:30:26.510 --> 00:30:31.610
are using the ERGs as
business resource groups.

00:30:31.610 --> 00:30:34.340
And they are being
valued even more

00:30:34.340 --> 00:30:36.690
and being brought
into the business.

00:30:36.690 --> 00:30:40.880
And that's really
helpful for employees.

00:30:40.880 --> 00:30:44.910
And it's helpful for
companies as well.

00:30:44.910 --> 00:30:45.730
Great questions.

00:30:45.730 --> 00:30:46.610
AUDIENCE: I actually
have one more question.

00:30:46.610 --> 00:30:47.880
CAROL FULP: Yes, please.

00:30:47.880 --> 00:30:50.010
AUDIENCE: Do you find that
there's any particular--

00:30:50.010 --> 00:30:52.468
